{
	"addonId": "universalTuner",
	"displayName": "Universal Tuner for NVDA",
	"URL": "https://github.com/sharetoyouaccess/UniversalTuner-/releases/download/v2.5.3/UniversalTunerV2.5.3.nvda-addon",
	"description": "\nAccessible instrument tuner for NVDA with reference tone playback for over two dozen instruments and tunings.\nLive microphone tuning: press L to listen while you play a string. Every 2 seconds it reports one clear reading: in tune, sharp by a percentage, or flat by a percentage (100% equals one semitone). Press C to switch to chromatic mode, which detects the nearest note automatically instead of comparing against a specific selected string.\nWhen a reading is exactly in tune, it plays a confirmation beep at the actual target note's pitch, then announces the note name. Press O to turn this beep on or off if you only want the spoken reading. Press R to repeat the last reading if you didn't catch it clearly. While live listening is on, Space cancels an in-progress beep and announcement immediately.\nSettings (A4 reference pitch, volume, tone length, gap, sample rate, chromatic mode, beep length, beep on/off, microphone device, last instrument and tuning) persist across NVDA restarts.\n",
	"sha256": "aa5fab6ee9d60714924bf5b880f839666ee215c7631f29cc76289e88832a1990",
	"addonVersionName": "2.5.3",
